4. NOUN USE REMAIN, STAY, OR CONTINUE TO HAVE/DO keep /kiːp/ CET4 TEM4 (keeping,kept,keeps) 

1. V-LINK If someone keeps or is kept in a particular state, they remain in it. 保持 (特定状态) 

例： The noise kept him awake. 噪音使他一直醒着。 

例： People had to burn these trees to keep warm during harsh winters. 在寒冷的冬天，人们得靠烧这些树保暖。 

2. V-T/V-I If you keep or you are kept in a particular position or place, you remain in it. 留在 

例： Keep away from the doors while the train is moving. 列车运行时请远离车门。 

例： He kept his head down, hiding his features. 他一直低着头藏住脸。 

3. V-I If you keep off something or keep away from it, you avoid it. If you keep out of something, you avoid getting involved in it. 避开 

例： I managed to stick to the diet and keep off sweet foods. 我设法坚持节食，不吃甜食。 

4. V-T If you keep doing something, you do it repeatedly or continue to do it. 继续 

例： I keep forgetting it's December. 我总是忘了现在是12月份。 

5. PHRASAL VERB Keep on means the same as keep . 继续 

例： Did he give up or keep on trying? 他是放弃了，还是在继续努力？ 

6. V-T Keep is used with some nouns to indicate that someone does something for a period of time or continues to do it. For example, if you keep a grip on something, you continue to hold or control it. 继续 (持有或控制) 

例： Until last year, the regime kept a tight grip on the country. 直到去年，该政权一直牢牢地控制着这个国家。 

7. V-T If you keep something, you continue to have it in your possession and do not throw it away, give it away, or sell it. 保留 

例： We must decide what to keep and what to give away. 我们必须决定哪些该留、哪些该扔。 

8. V-T If you keep something in a particular place, you always have it or store it in that place so that you can use it whenever you need it. 保存 

例： She kept her money under the mattress. 她把钱存放在床垫下面。 

9. V-T When you keep something such as a promise or an appointment, you do what you said you would do. 信守 

例： I'm hoping you'll keep your promise to come for a long visit. 我希望你会信守诺言，来这里多呆一段时间。 

10. V-T If you keep a record of a series of events, you write down details of it so that they can be referred to later. 记录 

例： Eleanor began to keep a diary. 埃莉诺开始记日记了。 

11. V-I If food keeps for a certain length of time, it stays fresh and suitable to eat for that time. 保鲜 

例： Whatever is left over may be put into the refrigerator, where it will keep for 2-3 weeks. 所有吃剩下的东西都可以放进冰箱，可保鲜2至3周。 

12. V-I You can say or ask how someone is keeping as a way of saying or asking whether they are well. 保持健康 [only cont] 

例： She hasn't been keeping too well lately. 她最近身体一直不太好。 

13. PHRASE If you keep at it , you continue doing something that you have started, even if you are tired and would prefer to stop. 坚持 

例： It may take a number of attempts, but it is worth keeping at it. 可能需要多次尝试，但这件事值得坚持做下去。 

14. PHRASE If you keep going , you continue moving along or doing something that you have started, even if you are tired and would prefer to stop. 坚持下去 

例： She forced herself to keep going. 她强迫自己坚持下去。 

15. PHRASE If one thing is in keeping with another, it is suitable in relation to that thing. If one thing is out of keeping with another, you mean that it is not suitable in relation to that thing. 与… (不) 一致 

例： This is not in keeping with our objective of representing the community. 这与我们代表该社区的目标不一致。 

16. PHRASE If you keep it up , you continue working or trying as hard as you have been in the past. 坚持不懈 

例： There are fears that he will not be able to keep it up when he gets to the particularly demanding third year. 有人担心到了极其艰难的第3年他会坚持不下去的。 

17. PHRASE If you keep something to yourself , you do not tell anyone else about it. 对某事守口如瓶 

例： I have to tell someone. I can't keep it to myself. 我得告诉别人。我不能对此守口如瓶。 

18. PHRASE If you keep to yourself , you stay on your own most of the time and do not mix socially with other people. 不与人交往 

例： He was a quiet man who always kept to himself. 他不爱说话，总是独来独往。 

